# Environment per PC — Agent

## Where to look

- **Index and checklist:** id:env-pc-readme (.cursor/environment-pc/README.md)
- **Per-PC profiles:** .cursor/environment-pc/pc-office.md (pc-office), .cursor/environment-pc/pc-home.md (pc-home)
- **Machine-readable list:** .cursor/environment-pc/manifest.json (`pcs[].label`, `file`, `checklistRef`)

## When to use

- User asks how to open the project on a new PC, sync environments, or fix "рассинхрон окружений".
- User refers to **pc-office** or **pc-home** — resolve to the corresponding .md and describe or apply steps from there.
- **«Настроить под этот ПК» / first-time setup:** offer to run the first-run script, then execute it:
  - **Windows:** `npm run env:setup` or `.\scripts\setup-dev-env.ps1` (from repo root).
  - Script does: Node in PATH → npm install → npm rebuild better-sqlite3 → npm run preflight. Idempotent.
- If user declines the script: give the checklist from README.md and id:readme-node18 (scripts/README-node18.md); offer to run `npm install`, `npm rebuild better-sqlite3`, `npm run preflight` manually.

## Adding a new PC

- Create .cursor/environment-pc/pc-<name>.md with frontmatter `id`, `label`, `description`, `last_updated`; add the PC to the table in README.md and to manifest.json `pcs`.
